website_summaries.verdict: An especially healthy pellet formulated to provide mid-sized birds with the nutrition and essential nutrients they need, and this is a fantastic foundation for any cockatoo or cockatiel diet.
pros: Corn, soybean meal, millet, oats, barley, and wheat are the first 6 ingredients
Includes all of the vitamins and minerals cockatiels and cockatoos need
cons: A solid all-around formula, but it represents 80% of your bird’s diet
Be sure to supplement it with seeds and fruit

customer_reviews.title: 15 years and going strong.
customer_reviews.text: I've fed this to my cockateil for 11 years. He has only been sick one time and that was with a cold. This is is primary food and he gets seed cups a few times a weeks and a millet spray every once in a while as a treat and thrives on it. His plumage is smooth and glossy and he is talkative and playful all the time.
customer_reviews.author: Kathy D. Salinas

customer_reviews.title: Healthy main food source for small-medium parrots
customer_reviews.text: I have had pet birds for 25 years. Our avian vet recommended this as our birds’ main food source. It is very nutritious and doesn’t have any artificial coloring. We still supplement with fresh fruits and vegetables. I used this with Quaker parrots, cockatiels, budgies, and a peach faced lovebird. None of them developed diet-caused issues as they aged. My Quaker parrot is 25 years old and our vet said his diet-related health is excellent. I also found this the easiest pellet food to switch a bird over to from a seed-based diet.
customer_reviews.author: J

customer_reviews.title: Lots of Goodness for My Bird, but He's Never Excited to Eat it.

It took him about a day to even touch it. Now he knows what to expect, although what I have noticed is that he will dip it in water before he eats it. Maybe it tastes better or maybe to soften it? All in all, great product because of all the vitamins and minerals he needs. I just wish he was more excited to eat it! I guess nothing beats seeds.

customer_reviews.title: My Meyers parrot loves it
customer_reviews.text: My Meyers parrot never used pallets without coloring and I was skeptical , worrying that he wouldn't eat it. I do mix it with the other kind that has colorful fruit shaped pallets but he doesn't seam to mind and I am happy he eats less of the colored food.

customer_reviews.title: My Grey does not like to hold big pieces of food
customer_reviews.text: My Grey does not like to hold big pieces of food, unless it is REAL meat, so he digs right in to this food. Perfect size for him. He eats it instead of throwing it out.
customer_reviews.author: rehabber

customer_reviews.title: Nivasi's favorite food.
customer_reviews.text: My bird LOVES his Zupreem Natural. Even though he's a Hahn's macaw, he prefers the cockatiel sized pellets. He particularly likes dunking them in his water, much to the dismay of his owner (that would be me). Anyway, this food is nutritious, without any artificial coloring, and much cheaper and healthier than what you'll find in the store. It's very convenient to be able to order online and have it shipped in bulk.
customer_reviews.author: Jessica Willis

customer_reviews.title: Good birb food
customer_reviews.text: Good food for my cockatiel. I mix this, the seeds, and the fruit blend together in a big bowl that way he gets all of his nutrients.

customer_reviews.text: I haven't found a healthier brand yet. The birds enjoy it. Back when the birds arrived they had been on different foods. We had no problems switching to this brand.
